  <discussion type="conservation">of conservation concern;</discussion>
  <discussion>Pyrrocoma liatriformis is one of the dominants of virgin Palouse prairies and appears to be threatened. It is recognized by its hirsute stems, leaves, and phyllaries, and the small, pedunculate heads.</discussion>
